The paper deals with constrained submodular function maximization, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. However, the focus on contention resolution schemes and the use of polyhedral techniques suggest that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI), which are all relevant to the topic.
